In a fresh interview with Bolanle Olukanni on Channels Television, famous Nollywood actress Patience Ozokwor recounted how she got married at the tender age. Patience said she was told she couldn’t wait for the love of her life so she had to be married off at the young age by her parents. Sharing her experience in her marriage, she said it was very awful but had to endure in order not to disappoint her father because she loved him so much. According to her, divorce wasn’t an option for her, coming from a polygamous family and having a Christian background. She added that her husband was battling with a terminal disease so she had to find ways to take care of her children. The actress revealed that on one occasion, her husband who woke from coma felt surprised to see her around him regardless of what he was going through. 